temperature = float(input())
fahrenheit = (temperature * 9/5) + 32
print("{:.1f}".format(fahrenheit))

temperature = float(input()) # This line prompts the user to enter a temperature in Celsius degrees. 
The `input()` function retrieves a string entered by the user, then `float()` converts it to a floating-point number to enable calculations.

fahrenheit = (temperature * 9/5) + 32 # This line performs the conversion of temperature from Celsius to Fahrenheit 
using the conversion formula: multiplying the temperature in Celsius by 9/5, then adding 32.

print("{:.1f}".format(fahrenheit)) # This line prints the converted temperature in Fahrenheit with a precision of one digit 
after the decimal point using the `format()` method to format the output. The specification `"{:.1f}"` indicates that only one digit after the decimal point should be displayed.
